physical_examinations.relevant_findings: At age 11 years, the anterior chest wall demonstrates normal development and appears solid to palpation. The radiographs show incorporation of struts in the anterior chest wall without migration or fracture.
The width of the chest wall defect was approximately 6.5 cm. Postoperative improvement in pulmonary function was noted.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Significant improvement in pulmonary function after the reconstruction.
